circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery:
Decedent found in a canal off Green Rd and Military Rd in Mission, TX on July 16, 2021 positively identified by the Hidalgo County Sheriff's office thru fingerprints as DANIEL BLANCO CRUZ.
Decedent found in a canal off Green Rd and Military Rd in Mission, TX on July 16, 2021 by a construction worker. Closest numerical address is 33641 Border Fence Street, Mission, TX. Believed to possibly be an immigrant. Decedent was then taken to Hidalgo County Forensic Center for an autopsy and fingerprinted. 

On July 27th, 2021 the decedent was Positively identified by the Hidalgo County Sheriff's office thru fingerprints which resulted in the name DANIEL BLANCO CRUZ DOB: April 19, 1981 a Mexican National born in Naranjos Amatlan, Veracruz. The local Mexican Consulate office in McAllen TX was able to confirm the decedents name, date of birth and location of birth in their registry. 
Possible fathers name: Silvino Cruz Mar 
Possible mothers name: Braulia Cruz Mar
